Physical Quantities

Base quantities are the seven physical quantities of the SI system by which all other physical quantities are defined.

They are: mass, length, time, temperature, amount of substance, electric current and luminous intensity.

The SI base units are a choice of seven well-defined units which by convention are regarded as dimensionally independent: kilogram (kg), metre (m), second (s), ampere (A), kelvin (K), mole (mol). Candela (cd) is not in the syllabus.

