## LO (h) add and subtract coplanar vectors

### Equal vectors

Vectors are equal if they have the _same magnitude and direction_.

### Negative vector

The negative of a vector has the _same magnitude but opposite direction_.

Coplanar vectors are vectors that lie on the same plane (2-dimension).

Unlike scalar quantities, vector quantities cannot be added or subtracted using algebra. Instead a _vector diagram_ is needed.

### Vector Addition

_a. Triangle method_

Stack the vectors such that one vector has its tail placed at the tip of the previous vector.

The resultant vector is represented by the line with a _double arrow_ directed from the tail of the first vector to the tip of the last vector.

_b. Parallelogram method_.

Put the vectors to be added 'tail to tail'. Complete the parallelogram. The resultant vector is the diagonal from the tail of the two vectors to the other vertex of the parallelogram.

